claim.claim-text:
15. In a network apparatus in a mobile backhaul network, a method for implementing a transparent clock, the method comprising:
receiving a first timestamp from a network node;
receiving a trigger from an upper network layer upon detecting a received Precision Time Protocol (PTP) event message;
creating, with a processor, a second timestamp;
computing, with the processor, a residence time based on the first timestamp and the second timestamp;
updating, with the processor, a header in the PTP event message with the residence time; and
forwarding the PTP event message.
